children.name: Rules
children.text:
A bullseye lantern made of dried mushroom bark with a purple cap with white spots on top of it. There is no candle or wick within, only a small pair of tightly pursed lips. 
This lantern has two charges, regaining them both after a long rest. The lantern can also regain one charge if you feed it a bioluminescent insect. 
-You can spend one charge and squeeze the lantern as an action to cast Faerie Fire from the lantern, but effecting a 15ft cone coming from the lantern as it spews up green spores.
-You can spend one charge and punch the lantern as an action to make it shriek loudly. All creatures in a 15ft cone coming from the lantern must make a DC 13 Constitution saving throw, taking 2d6 thunder damage and getting stunned until the end of your next turn on a failed save. If a creature succeeds they take half damage and are not stunned.
